keywords = "Ageing, Skin diseases, Epidemiology, Prevalence, Incidence",
abstract = "Background
The human population is aging. A systematic summary of the epidemiology of skin diseases in the aged is lacking.
Methods
A systematic review was conducted including electronic database searches in MEDLINE, Embase, SCOPUS and Web of Science. The eligibility criteria were primary incidence and prevalence studies or secondary data analysis, English or German language, subjects being 65+ years and reported skin problems or diseases. Data extraction was conducted using a standardized data collection form and the methodological quality of included studies was assessed.
Results
