abstract = "Background
Heart failure (HF) prevalence is increasing with an aging population and associated increasing comorbidities, and an expected concomitant increase in prescribed non-cardiac medications. The need to comply with clinical practice guidelines for multiple disease states often leads to polypharmacy; which in turn increases risk of drug-drug interactions, adverse drug reactions and nonadherence.
Hypothesis
